30 specifically in the areas of education, health, economics,
31 political participation and empowerment, housing, employment,
32 civil rights, criminal justice, and race relations and to
33 draft policy recommendations for addressing those issues."
34 Section 2. Sections 36-13-51, 36-13-53, 40-9F-38, and
35 41-1-93, Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to make conforming
36 changes to read as follows:
37 "§36-13-51
38 (a) The office shall be managed by a Director of the
39 Alabama Office of Minority AffairsCivic Engagement, who shall
40 be appointed by and serve at the pleasure of the Governor. The
41 position of director shall be a Governor's cabinet position.
