59 "§36-13-53
60 The Advisory Committee on Minority AffairsCivic
61 Engagement is created to act as a resource for the director in
62 an advisory capacity. The committee shall be comprised of
63 representatives from various racial and ethnic communities,
64 female representation, state government officials, and experts
65 in education and work force. The committee shall be appointed
66 by and serve at the pleasure of the Governor."
67 "§40-9F-38
68 (a) There is established the Historic Tax Credit
69 Evaluating Committee, which shall review qualifying projects,
70 approve credits for projects, and rank projects in the order
71 in which the projects should receive tax credit reservations
72 based on criteria established by the commission. The
73 commission shall establish a review cycle for the committee
74 beginning on January 1, 2018, provided that the committee
75 shall meet at least quarterly unless no credits remain to be
76 allocated. The Commissioner of Revenue shall be a nonvoting
77 member of the committee and provide advisory and technical
78 support. The committee shall consist of the following:
79 (1) The Director of the Alabama Office of Minority
80 AffairsCivic Engagement.
81 (2) The Executive Director of the Alabama Historical
82 Commission.
83 (3) The Finance Director.
84 (4) The Director of the Alabama Department of Economic
