98 (b)(1) The Alabama Historical Commission shall adopt
99 rules that shall set forth guidelines to be used by the
100 committee in determining the allocation of credits. The
101 guidelines shall set forth factors to be considered by the
102 committee including all of the following:
103 a. The relative value of the proposed project to the
104 particular community, including the maintenance of the
105 historic fabric of the community.
106 b. The possible return on investment for the community
107 in which the proposed project is located.
108 c. The geographic distribution of projects.
109 d. The likelihood of the project proceeding without the
110 historic tax credit authorized in this article.
111 e. The strength of local support for the proposed
112 project.
