142 (2) Prevents an employee or a contractor of a state
143 agency, local board of education, or public institution of
144 higher education who provides, as part of his or her job
145 duties, orientation, course work, or training from responding
146 to questions that are raised by participants in the
147 orientation, course work, or training and that pertain to
148 divisive concepts or diversity, equity, and inclusion.
149 (3)a. Prohibits a public institution of higher
150 education from providing any instruction or taking any action
151 in furtherance of satisfying any accreditation standard or
